QEMU
====

QEMU is a generic and open source machine emulator and virtualizer.

synthmodem redistributes a prebuilt QEMU binary in the Windows
distribution at win/qemu/. The version distributed is QEMU 11.0.50.
The corresponding source tarball is vendored at:

  win/qemu-source/qemu-master.zip

This tarball corresponds exactly to the source from which the
distributed QEMU binary was built.

Upstream project:  https://www.qemu.org/
Upstream source:   https://gitlab.com/qemu-project/qemu

License
-------

QEMU is licensed under the GNU General Public License, version 2
(GPL-2.0). The complete GPL-2.0 text is at licenses/GPL-2.0.txt,
which is the same license that covers synthmodem itself.

Individual QEMU source files carry their own copyright headers;
those headers are preserved in the vendored source tarball.
The QEMU project's own top-level COPYING file (GPL-2.0) is included
verbatim in the source tarball.

This component is included only in the Windows distribution
(win/qemu/). It is not part of the Linux distribution.

Corresponding source
--------------------

GPL-2.0 §3(a) requires that the QEMU binary redistributed in
win/qemu/ travel with its complete corresponding source. That
obligation is satisfied by committing the source tarball to this
repository at win/qemu-source/qemu-master.zip. The source tarball
corresponds exactly to the binary: no QEMU source files are
modified by synthmodem. The top-level COPYING enumerates this
path in its GPL corresponding-source statement.
